  "name": "lounge",
  "description": "A mellow vibraphone glowing in a cozy lamplit room, bars humming with soft motor shimmer. Warm struck-metal bars with a gentle tremolo from a slow motor vane, mallets soft and round; a woody upright-bass thumb pluck walks gently underneath, bell-bars ping bright, a bowed-vibe bloom blooms lush and lamplit, a soft mallet-roll cluster shimmers, and a muted tap keeps cozy time. A major pentatonic @ A=432, additive and clean, late-evening but sunlit-warm — smiling, never somber.",
